OL,3,CCovid Inquiry: Care worker describes
OL,4,C'hardest day' losing three residents
OL,6,FProf. Stephen Barclay also told the
OL,7,FInquiry that his research found that a
OL,8,Ffailure to prioritise end-of-life care
OL,9,Fmay have contributed to shortages of
OL,10,Fequipment, medicines, and staff.
OL,12,FHe said the result was that many dying
OL,13,Fpeople did not receive the care that
OL,14,Fthey needed, and "died with avoidable
OL,15,Fsymptoms and distress".
OL,17,FMs Kaur went on to discuss the "mental
OL,18,Ftrauma" she experienced upon learning
OL,19,Fa friend, who was also a care home
OL,20,Fworker and the same age as her, had
OL,21,Fpassed away from Covid.
