OL,6,FMr Drakeford gave evidence to the UK
OL,7,FCovid-19 Inquiry in 2023, during which
OL,8,Fhe said that the UK-wide strategy for
OL,9,Fdealing with a civil emergency ` which
OL,10,Fthe Welsh Government relied on ` was
OL,11,F"inadequate" and "did not stand up to
OL,12,Fits major test".
OL,14,FHe had also echoed the evidence of
OL,15,Fother Welsh Government officials,
OL,16,Fsaying resources seemed to have been
OL,17,Fdiverted away from pandemic planning
OL,18,Fbecause of the need to prepare for the
OL,19,Fthreat of a no-deal Brexit.
